A suspected robber was killed and two others arrested in a Saturday morning raid in Isebania town, Kuria West.OCPD Evance Wanyonyi said the suspects had been behind a series of crimes in the area and neighbouring Tanzania. He said officers had been searching for them. Wanyonyi said they killed 26-year-old Mwita Wandiki after members of the public informed them about a robbery.He said he was the gang leader and that he had shot at them.Wandiki's accomplices 20-year-old Kilo Wandiki and Charles Sope, 21, were placed in police custody.Wanyonyi said they recovered an AK47 rifle, 28 bullets, a motorcycle that the suspects used, Sh13,500 and two cell phones.He praised the public for working with police.